The paper discusses the use of visualization in various domains and presents a framework for conducting workshops to explore new applications of visualization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Visualization (cs.VIS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of workshops to accelerate the early stages of applied work, which could be relevant to the Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents a process model and actionable guidelines for conducting workshops, which could be relevant to the Social and Information Sciences (cs.SI) sub-category.
